<MudText Class="pa-5" Typo="Typo.h5">The Passion Project</MudText>
<MudText Class="pa-10">
	Game development started during the COVID lockdown in 2020. At the time there was a brief pause in training during which I looked into otherscripting languages initially 
	where I could create compoarisons between what I was teaching in Python and other languages. At the time Unreal Engine and Unity were everywhere and there was a big push from both companies by release learning material for free.
	Due to hardware constraints and the ease of the C# language (and the Unity UI seemed more approachable) I started to learn Unity. Here I began with basic tutorials and gradually ventured into more intermediate subjects. such as;
	<ul class="pa-5 mx-5 ">
		<li>Event based exectution - interactable items are wide ranging.</li>
		<li>Basic AI programming - simple decision making and behaviour trees.</li>
		<li>Multiple scence/project interaction - reducing the need for explicit singleton use.</li>
		<li>Scripting - Ranging from character movement scripting, interaction through event-driven principles.</li>
		<li>UI Design - both using the traditional Unity method of GameObjects and UI Toolkit which is XML/CSS based.</li>
		<li>Game Cinematics and asset management.</li>
	</ul>
</MudText>


